        "text": "*[Bug 16135] error in: convolve( 1:5, 1, type='filter')*\n<https:\/\/bugs.r-project.org\/show_bug.cgi?id=16135>\n\nMichael Chirico (<mailto:michaelchirico4@gmail.com|michaelchirico4@gmail.com>) changed:\n\n           What    |Removed                     |Added\n----------------------------------------------------------------------------\n                 CC|                            |michaelchirico4@gmail.com\n\n--- Comment #4 from Michael Chirico (<mailto:michaelchirico4@gmail.com|michaelchirico4@gmail.com>) ---\nCreated attachment 3611\n  --&gt; <https:\/\/bugs.r-project.org\/attachment.cgi?id=3611&amp;action=edit>\nUpdated convolve patch with ?convolve improvements and tests\n\nA few observations:\n\n`?convolve` has [1]\n\n&gt; numeric sequences _of the same length_ to be convolved.\n\nBut AIUI that is only required for `type=\"circular\"`, e.g. as written just\nbelow [2]:\n\n&gt; If `type == \"circular\"`, [`length(x) = length(y)`] is required\n\nNext, I'm no FFT expert, and I don't have access right now to the Brillinger\ntext linked at the end, but the wording here [3] isn't precise enough for me:\n\n&gt; For `\"open\"` and `\"filter\"`, the sequences are padded with `0`s (from left and right) first; `\"filter\"` returns the middle sub-vector of `\"open\"`, namely, the result of running a weighted mean of `x` with weights `y`.\n\nI think \"middle sub-vector\" in particular is not easily intuited.\n\nThe examples Benjamin provides with `y = rep(1, N)` imply the \"middle\nsub-vector\" is perhaps more easily understood as \"the sub-vector not requiring\n0-padding\" or \"the vector after filtering out those built from 0-padding\" or\nprecisely `k = m, ..., n` when `m&lt;=n` (using the index `k` from the formula\n[4]).\n\nThat would then imply that the wording \"namely, the result of running a\nweighted mean of `x` with weights `y`\" is _only for the `length(x)=length(y)`\ncase_.\n\nWith that preamble in mind, I am inclined to agree with Ben that this example\nis a plain bug -- the result should have length 5, not 3.\n\nThat said, I don't find Ben's patch satisfactory, since it will run into a\nsimilar edge case problem when `length(y) &gt; length(x)`, in which case we should\nreturn `numeric(0)`, because we always rely on 0-padding, as the current code\nachieves:\n\n```\n# under proposed patch\nconvolve(1:5, rep(1,6), type='filter')\n# [1] 15 15\n\n# in r-devel\nconvolve(1:5, rep(1,6), type='filter')\n# numeric(0)\n```\n\nI'm attaching a different patch to solve both problems, as well as taking a\nstab at improving the documentation.\n\nTracked at <https:\/\/github.com\/r-devel\/r-svn\/pull\/235>\n\n[1]\n<https:\/\/github.com\/r-devel\/r-svn\/blob\/5891760c29285562cfb0d1c5513625a93150e2a0\/src\/library\/stats\/man\/convolve.Rd#L17-L18>\n[2]\n<https:\/\/github.com\/r-devel\/r-svn\/blob\/5891760c29285562cfb0d1c5513625a93150e2a0\/src\/library\/stats\/man\/convolve.Rd#L46>\n[3]\n<https:\/\/github.com\/r-devel\/r-svn\/blob\/5891760c29285562cfb0d1c5513625a93150e2a0\/src\/library\/stats\/man\/convolve.Rd#L25-L28>\n[4]\n<https:\/\/github.com\/r-devel\/r-svn\/blob\/5891760c29285562cfb0d1c5513625a93150e2a0\/src\/library\/stats\/man\/convolve.Rd#L42-L44>",
