        "text": "*[Bug 19007] New: labels are not parallel to axes in persp() plot on Debian Linux*\n<https:\/\/bugs.r-project.org\/show_bug.cgi?id=19007>\n\n            Bug ID: 19007\n           Summary: labels are not parallel to axes in persp() plot on\n                    Debian Linux\n           Product: R\n           Version: R 4.5.x\n          Hardware: Other\n                OS: Linux-Debian\n            Status: UNCONFIRMED\n          Severity: normal\n          Priority: P5\n         Component: Graphics\n          Assignee: <mailto:R-core@R-project.org|R-core@R-project.org>\n          Reporter: <mailto:klaus.schliep@gmail.com|klaus.schliep@gmail.com>\n\nCreated attachment 3612\n  --&gt; <https:\/\/bugs.r-project.org\/attachment.cgi?id=3612&amp;action=edit>\nsimple persp plot with labels not parallel to the axes\n\nUsually (axis) labels in the `persp()` function are parallel to the axes. \nUnder Debian (I tested Debian trixie, SID and WSL with Debian) the labels are\nnot parallel to the axes (see attachment).\nWindows and WSL with Ubuntu is ok. So this seems mainly a Debian issue. \nI have no idea if the error is hardware dependent, I could only test on amd64. \n\nI compiled R-devel to see if the error is still there, and it is. But compiling\nwas really smooth and fast nowadays, huge compliment!!\n\nThe error seems related with the setting of the configuration variable\n`HAVE_ATAN2PI`. \nI compiled R-devel (R-devel_2026-02-20_r89442.tar.gz) and could fix it locally\nby editing out some lines. In R-devel\/src\/library\/graphics\/src\/plot3d.c  around\nline 806ff are two options and if I leave only the line \n```\nangle = (180. \/ M_PI) * atan2(dy, dx);\n```\nthe labels are parallel.   \n\nKind regards, \nKlaus Schliep",
